entries.femaleVariant: Still hangin' around with this punk?
Shut it, Harold. I know what you did.
Not about to ask why you covered it up. Not even why you jumped into this mess to begin with. Just wanna know – who gave you the order?
What's it matter, River? Why d'you even care? Your conscience is clear, you can sleep tight at night.
Ya know why? 'Cause I took all the responsibility.
You got no idea how this city works. Think your goddamn inspirational, idealist bullshit actually means something? It doesn't, never did.
'Ey, don't look at me that way, merc. You know I'm right.
Don't drag me into this.
Yeah. Night City born and bred.
Know the rules of the game.
No, not from here.
I know this town inside out.
I know the game NC makes you play. Know the rules, all the tricks in the book.
entries.maleVariant: I know the game NC makes you play. I know the rules, all the tricks in the book.

entries.femaleVariant: Not from here. Came from nowhere.
Hey, don't drag me into this. I don't do politics or NCPD inner-squabbles.
entries.maleVariant: 'Ey, don't drag me into this. I don't do politics or NCPD inner-squabbles.

entries.femaleVariant: So you know how it works. At city hall, in the street – rules are the same. Rhyne knew it too.
So you oughta know when to get in line, and when you can stick your neck out.
Ah… Nomad.
See, the NCPD – that's my family, that's my clan.
Yeah, so what do you do? Lemme guess – whatever brings in the eds, huh? S'typical... I'm not surprised, but I'm not judging either.
Lookin' for a path and place in this damned city – all of us.
Family comes first.
You just don't break with your family. You don't turn your back on your people.
Bullshit.
Yep, family comes first. Can't argue with that.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, family comes first. Can't argue with that.

entries.femaleVariant: The city eats anyone who tries to go it alone.
Bull-fuckin'-shit, Han. Fraternity of city cops resembles a clan not at all.
Loyalty, a blood bond, serving an ideal greater than the individual... Need I go on?
Gotta know which way the wind's blowing.
There's a line, though.
Gotta know which way the wind's blowin'. Gotta know that before anyone else has realized there's a storm comin'.
But there's a line. Not every order's worthy of being followed.
Lemme tell you when I'll stop doin' what I'm told – when I retire. Not a day sooner.
Oughta consider doing the same, Ward.
Rhyne was effective.
Not my thing – politics.
Rhyne was an asshole but an asshole who got shit done. I remember what it was like before he was elected.
Also remember who stopped the Militech panzers when the NUSA tried to annex Night City.
Politics bores me to tears. Every mayor – same asshole, different suit.
Not every mayor saved the city from Militech panzers – back when the NUSA tried to take us.
But Rhyne did. Y'think people remember that? All that matters is his death, 'cause it reeks of scandal.
A path and place, yeah.
You don't know shit about me.
Lookin' for a path and place, that's right.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, lookin' for a path and a place, that's right.

entries.femaleVariant: Great. We understand each other.
Don't know fuck all about me. Don't even try and guess what I'm about.
Didn't mean no offense.
V. 'Preciate the help, but this isn't your biz. I'll take care of it.
Got a scroll, got a motive, got your confession. So yeah, you could be.
But it wouldn't make much sense. You don't even gotta say who ordered you to go and clean up. I know anyway.
So since even our brass's fingers are all over this, I gotta take it to Internal.
They won't do a thing either. Not to me. They'll put you in their sights, though…
Just go home, Ward. Get some sleep. Find all this easier to take in in the morning.
I mean, that's my plan.
What're you gonna do?
Fuck.
Ughh...
So, what now?
Won't let this go. Can't.
Sounds about right.
Got no proof.
Also think it was Holt. Only one who stood to gain.
Even if that's what happened, don't have any solid proof.
Takin' this to Internal Affairs.
Go ahead.
Don't do it.
Got enough to get this case reopened.
Do it.
Don't do it. They'll sack you, or worse.
Besides, won't change a thing.
entries.maleVariant: Besides, it won't change a thing.

entries.femaleVariant: And you? Gonna report back to the Peralezes?
He fought for this city, cleanly at times, dirty at others, but always with a lotta heart.
Wouldn't've wanted him to get dragged through the muck.
'Cause stick it out at the wrong time and there'll always be some shark ready to bite your head off.
How you gonna do that? Am I under arrest?
He was right, sort of.
Shoulda shot him.
Han was right, sort of. Was just followin' orders. Even if he ends up payin' for it, system won't change.
entries.maleVariant: Han was right, sort of. Was just following orders. Even if he ends up payin' for it, system won't change.

entries.femaleVariant: Should've fed him some lead as a goodbye. Only way to be sure.
Holt murdered Rhyne. Wanted his seat. Oldest, tritest motive in the book. That's why I believe it.
Used the NCPD to cover his tracks.
I can't let it go, V. I can't and I won't.
Maybe it is.
But it's not my way, V.
Nah, wasn't like that.
No, wa'n't like that, not quite.
entries.maleVariant: No, wasn't like that, not quite.

entries.femaleVariant: Got a BD that somebody spiked. Just gotta figure out who. And that I think I can do.
So what happened?
Dunno. Just feel like this goes deeper than you, me, Han and Holt.
We'll prolly never know who was behind all this.
Could be right, you and Han.
But I couldn't give a shit what you two think.
Yep.
OK. I'm gonna stay, observe a little. Thanks, V.
[Get out]
